echnology, Willem H. Vanderburg's Our War on Ourselves explores the type of war we have unleashed on our lives by emphasizing discipline-based processes. The work also illuminates how we can achieve a more balanced, livable, and sustainable future by combining technical and cultural perspectives in our educational and institutional settings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDecision makingxSocial aspects. 0aEconomic developmentxSociological aspects. 0aSciencexSocial aspects. 0aSymbolism. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspects. 4aDISCOUNT-A. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269979340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442699793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442699793.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK